data.title: VSCode exits when launching extension tests
data.body:
- VSCode Version: 0.10.12-alpha
- OS Version: Windows 10

Steps to Reproduce:
1. clone https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode-languageserver-node
2. co dbaeumer/14
3. switch to client & npm install & npm run compile
4. switch to client.test & npm run compile
5. Open code on client-test
6. Press F5 to debug / run client tests

The dev instance of VSCode appears and then both renders including the main process disappear. Not sure if this is a crash or some sort of exit.

data.title: Telemetry error log is flooded
data.body:
It seems that the new insiders build (0.10.13, 0.10.14) generates far more telemetry error entries than before. It's too many to process by the telemetry tracker.
- The entries are not correctly folded, due to the specific extension path in the trace
  TypeError: Cannot read property 'document' of undefined 
  at Function.readLineAt (C:\Users\a123.vscode-insiders\extensions\vscodevim.vim-0.0.15\out\src\textEditor.js:65:53)
- We might want to turn of reporting logs for all extensions, although it is interesting to see commonly made errors, e.g, https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/issues/5022

data.title: TypeError: Cannot read property 'document' of undefined
data.body:
Our error telemetry reports now also reports issues for extension.
The 'Cannot read property 'document' of undefined' occurs for may different plugins, e.g.
- https://github.com/spywhere/vscode-guides/issues/2
- https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/issues/5007
- .vscode-insiders/extensions/mitaki28.vscode-clang-0.2.0/out/src/extension.js:71:55 
- .vscode-insiders/extensions/Ionide.Ionide-fsharp-1.5.2/fsharp.js:3142:34

Wondering if these are related and if we should do something about it (maybe better document it)
